{
  "text": "Finally, care should also be taken when selecting the time of the experiment, since prolonged exposure to temperatures above the melt temperature of the suspending polymers could lead to chemical changes in the sample [CITATION_1] . Furthermore, it is always recommended to perform rotational rheometry measurements in an oxygen-free atmosphere and not to use high shear rates. Polymer Rheology",
